xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Splitting Field</html:dfn> of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f(x)]]></fr:tex> over <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}]]></fr:tex> is an extension <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\Bbbk  / \mathbb {F}]]></fr:tex> such that
<fr:ol><fr:li><fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f(x)]]></fr:tex> factors completely over <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\Bbbk ]]></fr:tex>; and</fr:li>
<fr:li><fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f(x)]]></fr:tex> does not factor completely over a proper subfield of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\Bbbk ]]></fr:tex>.</fr:li></fr:ol></fr:p>
 
   
